29/04/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- US Ambassador Philip Reeker urged Macedonia on Wednesday (April 28th) to resolve its long-standing name dispute with Greece, saying its future depends on it. 
Reeker reaffirmed Washington's support for Skopje's European and Euro-Atlantic integration, adding Macedonia and Greece should look for a mutually acceptable solution to the row soon. 
Reeker also said that the international community strongly supports the Ohrid Framework Agreement. 
(MIA, A1, Radio Free Europe, Alsat - 28/04/10)
